<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="75" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="50.[811,1456,1380,1642]" pageId="50" pageNumber="75">
REMARKS. — Often included in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Temminck, 1820)" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1820" box="[1123,1451,1380,1405]" class="Aves" family="Laniidae" genus="Lanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="50" pageNumber="75" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis box="[1123,1263,1380,1404]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="75">L. meridionalis</emphasis>
(Temminck, 1820)
</taxonomicName>
, now considered monotypic (del 
<bibRefCitation author="HOYO J. &amp; DEL &amp; COLLAR N. J." box="[1119,1329,1407,1431]" pageId="50" pageNumber="75" refId="ref66516" refString="HOYO J. DEL &amp; COLLAR N. J. 2016. - HBW and BirdLife International Illustrated Checklist of the Birds of the World. Vol. 2. Passerines. Lynx Edicions, Barcelona, Spain and Cambridge, 1013 p." type="book" year="2016">Hoyo &amp; Collar, 2016</bibRefCitation>
), 
<emphasis box="[1345,1454,1407,1431]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="75">L. e. elegans</emphasis>
is the only subspecies certainly present in 
<collectingCountry box="[1221,1350,1433,1457]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="50" pageNumber="75">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
as a scarce dry season visitor (
<bibRefCitation author="BALANCA G. &amp; DE VISSCHER M. - N." box="[994,1268,1460,1484]" pageId="50" pageNumber="75" pagination="68 - 94" refId="ref64888" refString="BALANCA G. &amp; DE VISSCHER M. - N. 1997. - Composition et evolution saisonniere d'un peuplement d'oiseaux au nord du Burkina Faso (Nord-Yatenga). Malimbus 19: 68 - 94." type="journal article" year="1997">Balanca &amp; de Visscher 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="BORROW N. &amp; DEMEY R." pageId="50" pageNumber="75" refId="ref65136" refString="BORROW N. &amp; DEMEY R. 2001. - Birds of Western Africa. Christopher Helm, London, 832 p." type="book" year="2001">Borrow &amp; Demey 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The presence of 
<emphasis box="[1033,1169,1486,1510]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="75">L. e. leucopygos</emphasis>
Erhenberg, 1833, the subspecies breeding in 
<collectingCountry box="[973,1019,1513,1537]" name="Serbia" pageId="50" pageNumber="75">Mali</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1069,1126,1513,1537]" name="Niger" pageId="50" pageNumber="75">Niger</collectingCountry>
, in the extreme north of the 
<collectingCountry name="Burkina Faso" pageId="50" pageNumber="75">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
is also possible following 
<bibRefCitation author="BORROW N. &amp; DEMEY R." box="[1156,1408,1539,1564]" pageId="50" pageNumber="75" refId="ref65186" refString="BORROW N. &amp; DEMEY R. 2014. - Field Guide of the Birds of Western Africa. II edition. Christopher Helm, London, 592 p." type="book" year="2014">Borrow &amp; Demey (2014)</bibRefCitation>
. The taxonomy of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[979,1091,1566,1590]" class="Aves" family="Laniidae" genus="Lanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="50" pageNumber="75" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="excubitor">
<emphasis box="[979,1091,1566,1590]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="75">L. excubitor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex is very complicated and not fully resolved (
<bibRefCitation author="OLSSON U. &amp; ALSTROM P. &amp; SVENSSON L. &amp; ALABADIAN M. &amp; BERG P." box="[957,1137,1592,1616]" pageId="50" pageNumber="75" pagination="347 - 357" refId="ref67893" refString="OLSSON U., ALSTROM P., SVENSSON L., ALABADIAN M. &amp; SUND- BERG P. 2010. - The Lanius excubitor (Aves, Passeriformes) conundrum - Taxonomic dilemma when molecular and nonmolecular data tell different stories. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 55: 347 - 357." type="journal article" year="2010">
Olsson 
<emphasis box="[1032,1080,1592,1616]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
), and the assessment of 
<collectingCountry name="Burkina Faso" pageId="50" pageNumber="75">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
subspecies needs revision.
</paragraph>
